The paper deals with Fourier analysis and pseudorandomness, which are topics commonly studied in theoretical computer science. The use of Fourier analysis suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The study of pseudorandomness suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the mention of combinatorial rectangles suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
